Title: String-derived renormalization of Yang-Mills theory

Authors: Paolo Di Vecchia, Alberto Lerda, Lorenzo Magnea, Raffaele Marotta,

Rodolfo RussoComments: 11 pages. Latex, uses espcrc2.sty. Proceedings Buckow '95

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys.Proc.Suppl. 49 (1996) 85-95

We review the application of bosonic string techniques to the calculation ofrenormalization constants and effective actions in Yang-Mills theory. Wedisplay the multiloop string formulas needed to compute Yang-Mills amplitudes,and we discuss how the renormalizations of proper vertices can be extracted inthe field theory limit. We show how string techniques lead to the backgroundfield method in field theory, and indicate how the gauge invariance of themultiloop effective action can be inferred form the string formalism.(Proceedings of the 29th International Symposium on the Theory of ElementaryParticles, Buckow (Germany), Aug.-Sept. 1995. Preprint DFTT 04/96)